                    <span>You can not get any of the sample code to compile in Visual Studio 2003.  compiler kicks out error after error in the debugger.  Invalid parameters, null reference, etc. etc. after chapter 3 forget about debugging.  Hours and hours of researching MSDN and still no executeable code.  So once again, you can create that pretty little 3 colored triangle, thats about it. When are "experts" ever going to give us some practical learning tools?  C# the OOP oops! :grumbles: SOS!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Good start</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
